1. What is Helm? (Theory)
Helm is the package manager for Kubernetes/OpenShift.
Just like:
•	apt installs packages in Ubuntu
•	yum/dnf installs packages in RHEL
👉 Helm installs applications in Kubernetes using packages called Charts.
A Helm Chart contains:
•	Kubernetes manifests (Deployment, Service, Route, etc.)
•	Templates
•	Default configuration values
So instead of writing many YAML files manually, you run one Helm command.
Example:
helm install myapp nginx-chart
Helm automatically creates:
•	Deployment
•	Service
•	ConfigMaps
•	Routes
•	other resources
________________________________________
2. Important Helm Concepts
Chart
A chart is a packaged Kubernetes application.
Example:
etherpad chart
nginx chart
prometheus chart
________________________________________
Repository
A repository stores Helm charts.
Example repository URL:
http://helm.ocp4.example.com/charts
Works like:
•	Docker registry
•	yum repo
________________________________________
Release
A release is a running instance of a chart.
Example:
helm install example-app etherpad
Here:
example-app = release name
etherpad = chart name
You can install same chart multiple times with different release names.
Example:
helm install dev etherpad
helm install prod etherpad
