4. Check Existing Helm Repositories
Command:
helm repo list
Output:
Error: no repositories to show
Meaning:
👉 No chart repositories are configured.
________________________________________
5. Add Helm Repository
Command:
helm repo add do280-repo http://helm.ocp4.example.com/charts
Explanation:
Part	Meaning
helm repo add	add new chart repository
do280-repo	local name for repo
URL	where charts are stored
Output:
"do280-repo" has been added
________________________________________
6. Search Charts in Repository
Command:
helm search repo --versions
Example output:
NAME                     CHART VERSION
do280-repo/etherpad      0.0.7
do280-repo/etherpad      0.0.6
Meaning:
Chart etherpad has two versions:
0.0.6
0.0.7
________________________________________
7. View Default Chart Configuration
Command:
helm show values do280-repo/etherpad --version 0.0.6
This shows default configuration parameters.
Example:
replicaCount: 1
Meaning:
Default number of pods = 1
________________________________________
Example:
image:
  repository: etherpad
  tag: latest
Meaning:
Default image:
docker.io/etherpad/etherpad:latest
