So we must use local registry.
________________________________________
8. Create Custom Configuration (values.yaml)
Create file:
values.yaml
Content:
image:
  repository: registry.ocp4.example.com:8443/etherpad
  name: etherpad
  tag: 1.8.18

route:
  host: development-etherpad.apps.ocp4.example.com
Why?
To override chart defaults.
Default image:
docker.io
Custom image:
registry.ocp4.example.com
Also set custom route hostname.
________________________________________
9. Login to OpenShift
Command:
oc login -u developer -p developer https://api.ocp4.example.com:6443
Explanation:
Part	Meaning
oc login	login to cluster
-u developer	username
-p developer	password
URL	OpenShift API
________________________________________
10. Create Project (Namespace)
Command:
oc new-project packaged-charts-development
Explanation:
Creates namespace for application.
Result:
packaged-charts-development
________________________________________
11. Install Helm Chart
Command:
helm install example-app do280-repo/etherpad \
-f values.yaml --version 0.0.6
Explanation:
Part	Meaning
helm install	install chart
example-app	release name
do280-repo/etherpad	chart
-f values.yaml	custom config
--version 0.0.6	chart version
Helm will create:
Deployment
Service
Route
Pods
________________________________________
12. Check Application Route
Command:
oc get route
Example output:
example-app-etherpad
development-etherpad.apps.ocp4.example.com
Meaning:
Application URL:
https://development-etherpad.apps.ocp4.example.com
________________________________________
13. Verify Installed Helm Releases
Command:
helm list
Example output:
NAME         NAMESPACE                    CHART
example-app  packaged-charts-development  etherpad-0.0.6
Meaning:
Release:
example-app
Chart version:
0.0.6
________________________________________
14. Upgrade Helm Chart
New version available:
0.0.7
Upgrade command:
helm upgrade example-app do280-repo/etherpad \
-f values.yaml --version 0.0.7
Explanation:
Part	Meaning
helm upgrade	update release
example-app	release name
chart	same chart
values.yaml	config
version	new version
Output:
REVISION: 2
Meaning:
Deployment updated.
________________________________________
15. Deploy Production Version
Create production namespace.
oc new-project packaged-charts-production
________________________________________
16. Edit values.yaml
Change route:
route:
  host: etherpad.apps.ocp4.example.com
________________________________________
17. Install Production Deployment
Command:
helm install production do280-repo/etherpad \
-f values.yaml --version 0.0.7
Explanation:
production = release name
Now you have:
Development deployment
Production deployment
Both using same chart.
________________________________________
18. Check Pods
Command:
oc get pods
Example:
production-etherpad-xxxx
Pods running.
________________________________________
19. Scale Application
Edit values.yaml:
replicaCount: 3
Meaning:
Run 3 pods instead of 1.
________________________________________
20. Apply Changes
Command:
helm upgrade production do280-repo/etherpad -f values.yaml
Helm updates deployment.
________________________________________
21. Verify Scaling
Command:
oc get pods
Output:
production-etherpad-xxx
production-etherpad-xxx
production-etherpad-xxx
Now:
3 pods running
Load balancing works automatically.
________________________________________
22. Remove values.yaml
Command:
rm values.yaml
Cleanup file.
